        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName>
                <date>Febr'y 21<hi rend="sup">st</hi> 1855</date>.</p>
            <p>
                <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p>
                <add>Hebrew</add>
            </p>
            <p>
                <persName role="author">Michael Light</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <placeName>187 Forsyth <sic>street</sic></placeName>
            </p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName>, <date>February 21,
                1855</date></p>
            <p>Honored friend:</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Dr. Simon Abrahams</persName> told me that <persName>Mr.
                    Norr</persName> has been temporari-<lb/>ly elected steward of the hospital, and
                I therefore assume that <persName>Mr. Norr</persName><lb/> is disposed to accept
                this and that he will gladly take the post. I<lb/> have therefore declined to apply
                for the position of teacher at the<lb/> Hebrew Education Society and permit myself
                to ask you, in case you can<lb/> be of help to me in the attainment of a position of
                the said society<lb/> in <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>, to do so. For I am
                without a livelihood, “May God<lb/> reward you doubly in return”. In my letter to
                    <persName>Mr. Binswanger</persName>, I re-<lb/>ferred to you, and I ask you, in
                any event, to reply to this letter, and<lb/> to be good enough to let me know
                whether the teacher up till now will<lb/> remain or not, and how high the salary is,
                whether it is equal for<lb/> both teachers, etc., If there is no good prospect, I
                shall decide to<lb/> do something else. Herewith you receive also the enclosed card
                which<lb/> I have prepared without completing it for <persName>Mr. N.
                    Oettinger</persName>, since he ex-<lb/>plained to me that he himself hopes to
                sell the prayer books.</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">With <sic>th</sic> wish that this letter may find you in the best
                of<lb/> health, I sign with all respect,</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">Devotedly,</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">
                <persName role="author">Michael Light</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(11)">
                <placeName>187 Forsythe Street</placeName>
            </p>
        </body>
